      <p noindent="true">
	The monster is composed of a large number of smaller individuals.
	Swarms automatically hit against an armour defence.  Swarms suffer
	maximum damage from area of effect attacks like fire (any damage immunity applies).
	Swarms are not stopped by doors or windows or sometimes even walls.  GMs may make a swarm check
	each round to see if the swarm can pass through a barrier,<eg/> wall, window or door.  The difficulty
	of the check should depend on the integrity of the barrier.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>     
